main event: A bright flash that looked like a shooting star was observed moving erratically close to the horizon at Webb AFB, Texas.
interesting points: The object moved on a more level than downward path, unlike a typical shooting star.
The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes.
The object was observed at elevation angles of around 13 degrees and azimuth angles between 260-290 degrees.
The report was submitted by a military source (Ground-Visual observation).
The report includes a mention of photographs being taken, although no photographs are present in the provided image.
sighted object: a bright flash that looked like a shooting star but moved erratically
